10/07/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- State Department spokesman Philip Reeker on Wednesday (9 July) welcomed a statement by the leaders of Kosovo, who urged all refugees to return to the province. "This invitation is an unprecedented step by Kosovo political leaders to actively encourage the return of non-ethnic Albanians," he said. President Ibrahim Rugova, Prime Minister Bajram Rexhepi, Assembly President Nexhat Daci, and the former leaders of the KLA issued the statement on 2 July.
In other news, four ethnic Albanian children appeared before a court in Belgrade as witnesses in the trial of a Serbian special police officer. The children identified Sasa Cvjetan as the man who led the unit that executed 19 of their relatives in Podujevo on 28 March 1999. (AP, AFP - 09/07/03)
